From: Chunbo Luo <chunbo.luo@windriver.com>
Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2009 17:01:46 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] disable the selection of module for Cavium's watchdog

Change CAVIUM_OCTEON_WATCHDOG from tristate to bool because
the Cavium's watchdog cannot be compiled as a kernel module.

Signed-off-by: Chunbo Luo <chunbo.luo@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Kconfig b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Kconfig
index 5c5be0d..9a26969 100644
--- a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Kconfig
@@ -250,7 +250,7 @@ config CAVIUM_OCTEON_MGMT_PORT_ETHERNET
 	  CN57XX, CN56XX, CN55XX, and CN54XX chips.
 
 config CAVIUM_OCTEON_WATCHDOG
-	tristate "Octeon watchdog driver"
+	bool "Octeon watchdog driver"
 	default n
 	help
 	  This option enables a watchdog driver for all cores running Linux. It
